<body><p>GE.<footnote name="1">A/HRC/21/34.  </footnote>2-16917 
</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-first session 
</b></p>
<p>Agenda item 10 
<b>Technical assistance and capacity-building 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Senegal (on behalf of the African Group): draft resolution 
</b></p>
<p><b>  21</b>/&#8230;<b> Technical assistance and capacity-building for South Sudan  
   in the field of human rights 
</b></p>
<p><i>The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p><i>Guided by</i> the principles and objectives of the Charter of the United Nations, the 
Universal Declaration of Human Rights, the African Charter on Human and Peoples&#8217; 
Rights and relevant human rights treaties, 
</p>
<p><i>Emphasizing</i> that States have the primary responsibility for the promotion and 
protection of all human rights, 
</p>
<p><i>Welcoming</i> the commitments made by the Government of South Sudan to strengthen 
national mechanisms of promotion and protection of human rights, and calling on the 
Government to implement those commitments, 
</p>
<p><i>Recognizing </i>the challenges of institution and State building facing South Sudan, and 
commending the steps being taken to address those challenges, 
</p>
<p>1. <i>Takes note</i> of the report of the United Nations High Commissioner for 
Human Rights on technical assistance and capacity-building for South Sudan in the field of 
human rights;1 
</p>
<p>2. <i>Encourages</i> the Government of South Sudan, by its continuous commitment, 
to resolve all outstanding issues subsequent to the Comprehensive Peace Agreement of 
2005 with the Government of the Sudan; 
</p>
<p>3. <i>Requests </i>Member States, relevant United Nations agencies and stakeholders 
to support, as a matter of urgency, the national efforts of the Government of South Sudan, 
in accordance with Human Rights Council resolution 18/17 of 29 September 2011 on 
technical assistance and capacity-building; 
</p>
<p>4. <i>Requests</i> the Office of the High Commissioner to provide South Sudan with 
the necessary technical support and training; 
</p>

<p>5. <i>Also</i> <i>requests</i> the Office of the High Commissioner to submit a report on the 
progress of technical assistance and capacity-building for South Sudan to the Human Rights 
Council at its twenty-third session. 
</p>
<p> </p>

